var tipuesearch = {"pages":[{"title":" Fortran index ","text":"Fortran index Description Fortran index is an initiative born out of the Back to the Fortran Future satellite event of RSECon 2024 .\nOur mission is to make it easier for Fortran users and developers to find useful\nresources, such as tools, documentation, training materials... and anything else\nFortran-related. We work on improving Fortran indexing by making group contributions to the\nexisting fortran-lang website. The format for our\ncontributions is a sequence of semi-regular 2.5-hour hackathons. The Fortran index documentation pages provide information\nabout the hackathon series, how the hackathons work, how to get involved, and\nupcoming and past events.","tags":"home","url":"index.html"},{"title":"fortran_birthday – Fortran index","text":"Variables Type Attributes Name Initial character(len=70) :: date = \"2026-12-01\" character(len=70) :: location = \"Science and Industry Museum, Manchester\" character(len=70) :: intro = \"Welcome\" character(len=70) :: thank = \"Sponsor lightning talks\" character(len=70) :: keynote = \"Where we've been in the past 70 years\" character(len=70) :: lightning1 = \"TBD\" character(len=70) :: lightning2 = \"TBD\" character(len=70) :: lightning3 = \"TBD\" character(len=70) :: lightning4 = \"TBD\" character(len=70) :: lightning5 = \"TBD\" character(len=70) :: lightning6 = \"TBD\" character(len=70) :: announcement = \"FortranFuture\" character(len=70) :: breakout = \"The next 70 years\" character(len=70) :: outro = \"Closing, move to reception\"","tags":"","url":"program/fortran_birthday.html"},{"title":"fortran_birthday.f90 – Fortran index","text":"Source Code ! Programme for the 'Celebrating 70 years of Fortran' event program fortran_birthday implicit none character ( len = 70 ) :: date = \"2026-12-01\" character ( len = 70 ) :: location = \"Science and Industry Museum, Manchester\" ! Hello, World! character ( len = 70 ) :: intro = \"Welcome\" character ( len = 70 ) :: thank = \"Sponsor lightning talks\" ! Past character ( len = 70 ) :: keynote = \"Where we've been in the past 70 years\" ! Present: Exciting developments character ( len = 70 ) :: lightning1 = \"TBD\" character ( len = 70 ) :: lightning2 = \"TBD\" character ( len = 70 ) :: lightning3 = \"TBD\" ! Present: Community initiatives character ( len = 70 ) :: lightning4 = \"TBD\" character ( len = 70 ) :: lightning5 = \"TBD\" character ( len = 70 ) :: lightning6 = \"TBD\" ! Future character ( len = 70 ) :: announcement = \"FortranFuture\" character ( len = 70 ) :: breakout = \"The next 70 years\" character ( len = 70 ) :: outro = \"Closing, move to reception\" end program fortran_birthday","tags":"","url":"sourcefile/fortran_birthday.f90.html"},{"title":"Documentation – Fortran index","text":"Welcome to the Fortran index documentation! Here you can find information about the hackathon series, how the hackathons\nwork, how to get involved, and upcoming and past events. Click the links on the\nsidebar to get started.","tags":"","url":"page/index.html"},{"title":"Contribution guide – Fortran index","text":"Contribution guide Contents How to contribute How to get set up Upcoming and past events Fortran index contributions","tags":"","url":"page/contribution/index.html"},{"title":"How to contribute – Fortran index","text":"Contributing All are welcome to contribute to Fortran index, provided they abide by the code of conduct of the\nComputational Abilities Knowledge Exchange (CAKE) network. See the CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md file for more details. Please familiarise yourself with its terms before\nbeginning your contribution. Ways to contribute There are lots of ways to contribute to the Fortran index initiative, as\ndetailed below. Open an issue on the fortran-lang repository To propose an addition, correction, modification, restructuring, or removal from\nthe fortran-lang webpage , open an issue on\nthe fortran-lang webpage repository. Open a pull request on the fortran-lang repository If you have found or opened an issue in the fortran-lang webpage repository and would like to start work on it, first read the contribution guidelines . You\nwill likely need to fork the fortran-lang webpage repository before you can open a pull request. See the setup page for some tips related to this. Open an issue on the Fortran index repository To raise an issue related to how the Fortran index repository or documentation\nis structured, or to make a suggestion related to how the hackathon series is\nrun, raise an issue on the Fortran index repository. Attend a Fortran index hackathon The best way to get involved in the Fortran index initiative is to attend a\nhackathon. In these regular virtual events, contributors meet as a group to\ncombine our efforts. See the events page for information related to upcoming hackathons, including registration details. Get in touch For any other enquiries, please get in touch with the hackathon lead organiser Joe Wallwork ( @joewallwork , jw2423@cam.ac.uk ).","tags":"","url":"page/contribution/contributing.html"},{"title":"Setup – Fortran index","text":"Setup To set yourself up for contributing to Fortran index in one of the hackathons,\nprovide your GitHub username to one of the organisers, who will add you to the fortran-index GitHub organisation. Once you've been added, you will be able to\nclone the fortran-lang-webpage fork of https://github.com/fortran-lang/webpage . Beware that a straightforward clone of this fork will pull the entire Git\nhistory of the website, which is more than 50 GB. Instead, clone using git clone --filter=blob:none git@github.com:fortran-index/fortran-lang-webpage.git or git clone --depth=1 git@github.com:fortran-index/fortran-lang-webpage.git","tags":"","url":"page/contribution/setup.html"},{"title":"Upcoming and past events – Fortran index","text":"Events Information related to upcoming and past Fortran index events can be found in\nthe table below. Date Time Topic Registration Contributions 2025-02-11 13:30-16:00 (UTC) Packages Closed Info 2025-04-07 13:00-15:30 (BST) Packages Closed Info 2025-06-12 10:00-12:30 (BST) More info for packages and compilers Closed Info 2025-09-08 09:30-16:30 (BST) Strategy session at Back to the Fortran Future 2 workshop Closed Info 2025-12-15 14:00-16:30 (UTC) Info on why someone would use Fortran Closed Info 2026-01-26 14:00-16:30 (UTC) SIG-RPC collab Closed Info 2026-03-05 14:00-16:30 (UTC) Reworking of package index Closed Info 2026-05-01 09:30-15:30 (BST) Hack day at SSI Collaborations Workshop Closed Info 2026-06-16 16:30-18:00 (BST) Fortran community meetup, Durham HPC days Closed Info 2026-06-17 16:30-18:00 (BST) CAKE session, Durham HPC days Closed Info 2026-07-22 14:00-16:30 (BST) Reworking of package index https://forms.gle/7QjJjs5cDPt2Pbwg9 Info 2026-12-01 10:00-13:00 (UTC) In-person hackathon! TBD TBD 2026-12-01 15:00-20:00 (UTC) Celebrating 70 years of Fortran TBD TBD","tags":"","url":"page/contribution/events.html"},{"title":"Fortran index contributions – Fortran index","text":"Fortran index contributions Contributions made during Fortran index hackathons are recorded in the GitHub\nrepository in the contributions subdirectory.","tags":"","url":"page/contribution/contributions.html"},{"title":"Celebrating 70 years of Fortran – Fortran index","text":"Celebrating 70 years of Fortran Fortran has been supporting scientific software engineering and critical\ninfrastructure for 70 years. To celebrate this, we will be holding a 'birthday\nparty' on 1 December 2026 at the Science and Industry Museum , in\nManchester, UK. The timing was chosen to align with Computing Insights UK (CIUK) - 'the UK's premier conference for HPC and\nassociated research' - which will be held a short walk away between 2-4 December\n2026. Outline The birthday party event will have three parts: 10:00-13:00 - Small community meetings 15:00-18:15 - Main workshop (with provisional programme ) in the\n  museum conference suite 18:15-20:00 - Drinks reception in the exhibition hall by the Baby computer, which will be demonstrated Registration Attendance will be free of charge, thanks to the support of our funders and\nsponsors including Computational Abilities and Knowledge Exchange (CAKE) and the Institute of Computing for Climate Science (ICCS) . A full registration form will be reseased in due course. In the meantime,\nregister your interest by completing the 'save the date' form. More information If you have any questions about the event, please contact lead organiser Joe\nWallwork at jw2423[AT]cam.ac.uk. Key links 'Save the date' form to register interest Provisional workshop programme Blog post on CAKE fellowship and 70 years of Fortran","tags":"","url":"page/fortran_birthday.html"},{"title":"Funding – Fortran index","text":"Funding In January 2026, Fortran index lead organiser Joe Wallwork was awarded a\nComputational Abilities Knowledge Exchange (CAKE) fellowship to\nfurther the aims of the hackathon series. The funding will be used to attend the third Back to the Fortran Future workshop\nand the Software Sustainability Institute's Collaborations Workshop in Belfast\nin April 2026. The goal of attending these events is to expand the contributor\nbase for Fortran index. In particular, it would be beneficial to have insight\nfrom web developers and those with community sites for programming languages\nother than Fortran. The funding will also be used to host the first ever in-person Fortran index\nhackathon in Cambridge, UK, in autumn 2026. This will coincide with a birthday\nparty to mark 70 years since the first document related to Fortran was\npublished. More details related to these events will be posted in due course.","tags":"","url":"page/funding.html"},{"title":"Licensing – Fortran index","text":"MIT License Copyright (c) 2024 Fortran index Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy\nof this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal\nin the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights\nto use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell\ncopies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is\nfurnished to do so, subject to the following conditions: The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all\ncopies or substantial portions of the Software. THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR\nIMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,\nFITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE\nAUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER\nLIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,\nOUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE\nSOFTWARE. The Fortran index logo is based on the Fortran logo used by fortran-lang . Both use the Clarendon BT font.","tags":"","url":"page/licensing.html"}]}